Data Analysis to identify the potential customers who have a higher probability of purchasing the loan¶

The bank has customer data with various charectoristics of customers. They have built new product - personal loan and they are making campaign to attract more customers and last campaign has given 9% success. This has encouraged the retail marketing department to devise campaign with better target marketing to increase the sucess ratio with minimal budget

The main requirement :

1. To sell more personal lona products to Bnak customers
2. Better target marketing and increase the success ratio with minimul budget
3. Identify customers with higher probability of purchasing personal loan

Increase the success ratio but at the same time at less budget

Learnings from last campaign since bank got 9% success:

1. Is there any association between personal charectoristic and getting personal loan
2. What are those major charectoristics which has got association with personal and what is the strength of the association.

Objective: The classification goal is to predict the likelihood of a liability customer buying personal loans.

Steps and tasks:

  1. Readthecolumndescriptionandensureyouunderstandeachattributewell
  2. Study the data distribution in each attribute, share your findings
  3. Get the target column distribution. Your comments
  4. Split the data into training and test set in the ratio of 70:30 respectively
  5. Use different classification models (Logistic, K-NN and Naive Bayes) to predict the likelihood of a liability customer buying personal loans
  6. Print the confusion matrix for all the above models
  7. Give your reasoning on which is the best model in this case and why it performs better?

Information on the attributes : It can be devided as below

a. The variable ID does not add any interesting contribution. There is no association with personal loan and ccustomer ID. we can neglect this information.

The Binary category have five variables as below : a. Personal Loan - Did this customer accept the personal loan offered in last campaign? this is our target variable b.Security account - Does the customer have a securities account with the bank? c. CD account - Does the customer have a certification of deposit ( CD account) with the bank? d.Online - Does the customer use internet banking facility? e. Credit card - Does the customer use a credit card issued by Thera bank?

Interval Variables are as below : 

    1.Age - Age of the customer
    2.Experience - Years of experience
    3.Income - Annual income in dollars
    4.CCAvg - Average credit card spending
    5.Mortgage - Value of House Mortgage

Ordinal Categorical Variables are : 

    1. Family - Family size of the customer
    2.Education - Education level

The nominal variable is : 
    1. ID
    2.Zip Code

Observations as below :

1. AGE feature is normally distributed with majority of customers falling between 30~60 years of age. We can confirm this by looking at the describe statement above, which shows mean is almost equal to median.
2. EXPERIENCE is normally distributed with more customers haveing experince starting from 8 years. Here the mean is equal to median. there are negative values in the Experince. This could be a data input error as in general it is not possible to measure negative years of experince. We can delete these values.
3. INCOME is positively skewed.Majority of the customers have income between 45k to 55k. we can confirm this by saying the mean is greater than the median.
4. CCAvg is also a positively skewed variable and avarage spending is between 0k to 10K and majority spends leass than 2.5k
5. MORTAGE 70% of idividuals have a mortage of less than 40K.
6. The variables family and education are ordinal variables. The distribution of families is evenly distributes.

# for the record with the ID, get the value of Age column
# for the record with the ID, get the value of education column
# filter the records matching the above criteria from the data frame which has records with positive experiences and take the median
# apply the median back to the location which had negative experiences
In [16]:
for id in mylist:
    age = data.loc[np.where(data['ID']==id)]['Age'].tolist()[0]
    education = data.loc[np.where(data['ID']==id)]['Education'].tolist()[0]
    df_filter = PExp[(PExp.Age == age) & (PExp.Education == education)]
    exp = df_filter['Experience'].median()
    data.loc[data.loc[np.where(data['ID']==id)].index, 'Experience'] = exp

hence, in the current set of algorithms applied on the available data,it seems to be the best choice to predict the customers who will accept the personal loan.
